This paper discusses patterns of word use in online discussion communities, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also analyzes the relationship between words and their environments, which could be considered a form of social computing (cs.SI) or social dynamics (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper explores the dynamics of language adaptation, which could be relevant to the study of natural language processing (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the influence of individual proclivities on word fate, which could be considered a form of social computing (cs.SOC).
